ory, and the house where they took place is still there, along with a museum. There’s much more to Salem, however, including a <a href="https://www.pem.org/">fine maritime and cultural museum</a> and a seaport. (And don’t forget the clams.)</p><p>— Tom</p><p><i>Isabel Fattal contributed to this newsletter.</i></p>